6:
Hah-hah-hah! Is this what it is like to
have a brush with death? Well done,
my friends! Bask in my praise!
10:
But now that I have a moment to
think... Perhaps I could have even
taken them out by myself!
13:
Uh-huh. Sure, yep. I'm gonna ignore
your shaking knees and help you up
now.
18:
What is a Farlands prince like you
doing out here?
21:
Well, you see... I was on a tour
throughout the land when,
somehow, I became separated from
my tutor!
24:
Why am I not surprised he got lost
again...
30:
...You really are a prince of a large
kingdom then.
35:
Did you not trust my initial
introduction? I am who I say I am! Is
that so hard to believe?!
39:
Hello, my name is Stella. Who are
you?
44:
O-oh, sorry... I haven't even thanked
you for saving my life.
46:
I'm Simon. I appreciate you stepping
in when you did.
49:
This here is my home. It's not much,
but feel free to come in.
59:
Yes. The whole town and the castle
were all made by Princess Prika,
whom I serve.
63:
Hold up... You're telling me this was
the work of ONE person who used
magic and nothing else?
67:
Is this true?

...And to think you thought me the
liar earlier...
70:
I suppose it must seem strange to
outsiders. Only those of a special
bloodline are capable of such a
feat, but I've long grown
accustomed to seeing it.
73:
The poppets were also created by
the princess, though I don't
understand why they suddenly
attacked like that...
76:
I'm sorry, but can I impose on you
one more time? Could you check
the castle to see if the princess is
safe?
80:
Perhaps this is related to the
strange monsters emerging from
the forest...
83:
How about this: if you don't mind us
investigating a few matters along
the way, we'd be happy to look in on
her.
87:
That is completely fine by me.
Please do what you see fit.
91:
I still find it difficult to believe that
these grand structures are made of
magic and nothing more.
95:
Doesn't this place remind you of
Starview Village?
100:
I was actually thinking the same
thing when we first got here.
105:
Are you daft? How could an empty
ghost town like this compare to the
rowdy chaos of your lively home?
109: I cannot say I prefer such emptiness!
113:
That was not my fault! I swear I
merely breathed upon it!
116:
Relax, no one's going to scold you.
The way that thing crumbled
though...
120:
It makes one think this is a
decorative wonderland and not a
place for living in.
124:
More poppets! We'll have to fight
through them!
129:
These rascals again? Very well!
Surely this time you will take turns
and fight fairly, won't you?
